 _______________________________________________________________________

 Mandriva Linux Security Advisory                         MDVSA-2011:095
 http://www.mandriva.com/security/
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Package : apr
 Date    : May 20, 2011
 Affected: 2009.0, 2010.1, Corporate 4.0, Enterprise Server 5.0
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Problem Description:

 It was discovered that the fix for CVE-2011-0419 under certain
 conditions could cause a denial-of-service (DoS) attack in APR
 (CVE-2011-1928).
 
 Packages for 2009.0 are provided as of the Extended Maintenance
 Program. Please visit this link to learn more:
 http://store.mandriva.com/product_info.php?cPath=149&amp;products_id=490
 
 The updated packages have been patched to correct this issue.
 _______________________________________________________________________

 References:

 http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2011-1928
 _______________________________________________________________________

